VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)(os\.remove|os\.unlink|shutil\.rmtree)
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(request|input\(|argv|user_input|params|query) && MISSING:(abspath|realpath|normpath|startswith\(|allowlist|whitelist)
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the use of file removal functions in Python that may operate on untrusted file paths, potentially leading to security risks.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Insecure File Operations.
